      <p id="Par25">The original publication also investigates <italic>Lcn2</italic> at the exon-level using the differential splicing functionality of the TAC software. The MTA 1.0 array has 15 PSRids (8 targeting exons) and 5 JUCids targeting splice junctions for the <italic>Lcn2</italic> transcript (see Table <xref rid="Tab2" ref-type="table">2</xref>). The authors of the original publication deduce that the main transcript, Lcn2–201, is up-regulated rather than the only other protein-coding transcript variant, Lcn2–206 (see Figure 4.A from [<xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR19">19</xref>]).
